    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You cannot hear and suffer all of the usual penalties for being deafened. You cast all of your spells as if they were modified by the @Compendium[pf1.feats.2YuxcUNFMPNBpekG]{Silent Spell} feat. This does not increase their level or casting time.</p>\n<p>At 5th level, you receive a +3 competence bonus on Perception checks that do not rely upon hearing, and the initiative penalty for being deaf is reduced to â€“2.</p>\n<p>At 10th level, you gain scent and you do not suffer any penalty on initiative checks due to being deaf.</p>\n<p>At 15th level, you gain tremorsense out to a range of 30 feet.</p>",
